	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In case it hasn't been mentioned, changing the vscroll (which requires setting loopy_v), switching banks, or doing other stuff that affects rendering &quot;immediately&quot; probably can't be done without glitching during the last 20 ticks or so of hblank, as the first two tiles for the next scanline are fetched there - so the safe window might be slightly narrower than you expect.<br /><br />The diagram I made in <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=9901&amp;start=30">viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=9901&amp;start=30</a><!-- l --> might clarify this.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
